dct_title_s: Digital shaded relief maps of Israel
dct_description_sm: Geophysical Institute of Israel. Companion text: Geological framework of the Levant. Volume I: Cyprus and Syria. Volume II: The Levantine Basin and Israel / John K. Hall; Valey A. Krasheninnikov; Francis Hirsch; Chaim Benjamini; Akiva Flexer. Jerusalem: Historical Productions-Hall. 2005. North Decimal Degree 33.3333. South Decimal Degree 29.5000. East Decimal Degree 35.8833. West Decimal Degree 32.2000. Universal transverse Mercator projection. Recto: Map is plate XI. Relief shown by hypsometric tints. Verso: Map is the original grayscale shaded relief map of Israel (1:500,000).
